description: Our family has owned this Ski Boat since my father purchased it in 1990 .  This boat has been stored indoors and well kept.  Countless family excursions have been made to most of the lakes in the Kansas and Missouri area.  Trailer is in good condition too and has been very road worthy.  It is an open bow and comfortably seats 6 adults but up to 8 if small children.  Skiing, tubing, and wake boarding are great behind this boat.  I had the motor cover remade and re-apoltered about 5 years ago, as well as we put in a new floor and carpet.  We also re-apolstered the back two seats next to the motor cover and the rear canopy cover.  The seats in the open bow now need to be done but other than that the interior is in very good condition and with very little sun damage to the red and white interior colors this a very sharp boat.  The Gray exterior also is in good condition making this boat look much newer than it's actual age.  I have not de-winterized the boat this season. The boat will also need a new battery, I'm guessing, and the motor and trim package will need a tune-up.  Last time we had it out it was running great (2015).  I would like to sell, as is.  As much as I hate to part with this boat my family is ready for a newer model and I would like to sell before looking for a new one.
